The Diaspora Support  comprising Nigerians in the diaspora, has  tipped a former Governor of Lagos state and national leader of the All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, Governors of Sokoto State, Aminu Tambuwal, and Rivers State, Nyesome Wike  as credible presidential candidates in the 2023 polls. Tambuwal and  Wike are of the main opposition Peoples Democratic Party while Tinubu is a chieftain of the APC. The two governors were rumoured to be nursing presidential ambition while Tinubu has declared  his intention to vie for the  coveted office. The group said the trio were picked among prominent Nigerians as possible credible materials for the forthcoming presidential election in the country. According to a statement issued by the Convener of the group, Yunana Shibkau, and the  Head of Strategy and International  Mobilization,  Osamudiamen Aghedo, ’’there is nothing wrong with ‘Muslim – Muslim’ and as well as ‘Christian-Christian’ tickets for the 2023 Presidency.’’ The TDS’ statement titled, ‘2023: Nigerians in diaspora endorse Tambuwal, Tinubu and Wike,’ was made available in Kaduna on Friday. The group also bemoaned the state of the nation which they described as appalling in terms of declined standards of living of Nigerians as well as the insecurity across the country. They also called on Nigerians in respective of religion or tribe to support candidates that would unite the country. The statement read, “We noted with regrets how the country has rapidly declined in standard of living, occasioned by galloping inflations that had deepened the poverty of the people and multiplied their miseries in the process.” Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com